{"profile":{"awsPrograms":[{"joinedAt":2026.0,"programName":"USER_GROUP_LEADER"},{"joinedAt":2026.0,"programName":"NEW_VOICES"},{"category":"Security Hero","joinedAt":2023.0,"memberStatus":"ACTIVE","programName":"HERO"}],"basicInfo":{"alias":"gerardokaztro","avatar":"https://avatars.builderprofile.aws.dev/3AUftb5EfAV7FxvC3B3NYN6ZKHV.webp","bio":"AWS Security Hero | Cloud Security Engineer | Founder & Lead Organizer of AWS Security Users Group LatAm\n\nI specialize in cloud security for AWS multi-account environments, with a focus on automating security visibility across AWS Organizations. My work sits at the intersection of hands-on engineering and practical security — building real tools that solve real problems in production environments across LATAM.\n\nI believe the best way to learn cloud security is by building, not memorizing. Every post I write comes from something I actually built, broke, or discovered in the field.\n\nCurrently building iam-audit — an open source Python tool that audits IAM users, Access Keys, and root accounts across AWS Organizations, with an interactive HTML dashboard and Docker support. Available at github.com/gerardokaztro/iam-audit\n\nAs Founder and Lead Organizer of the AWS Security Users Group LatAm, I work to grow the cloud security community across the region — connecting engineers, sharing knowledge, and raising the security baseline one organization at a time.\n\nWriting about all of this at Road to CloudSec LATAM → roadtocloudsec.hashnode.dev","builderProfileId":"96c2bb8a-7402-401e-bcff-a236775d8e52","createdOn":1.70718855168E12,"isStaff":false,"name":"Gerardo Castro Arica"},"location":{},"profileStatus":"ACTIVE","socials":{"blog":"https://linktr.ee/gerardokaztro","devto":"https://dev.to/gerardokaztro","facebook":"","github":"https://github.com/gerardokaztro","linkedIn":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/gerardokaztro/","personal":"","repost":"","twitter":"https://x.com/gerardokaztro","youtube":"https://www.youtube.com/@gerardokaztro"}}}